<h1> Stashing Changes temporary storage without committing </h1>

<h2> Saving changes in the stash </h2>

```
$ git stash save "changed mission title"
    Saved working directory and index state On shorten_title: changed mission title
    HEAD is now at d13990f Added a colon in title to index.html
```

<h2> Viewing stashed changes</h2>

```
$ git stash list

# ### stash@{0} is how to reference, On the branch you were on
stash@(0}: On shorten_title: changed mission title

# ### You can pull the stash out in any branch by changing branch
$ git stash show stash@{0}
   mission.html | 2 +-
   1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

# ### to show more info use -p for --patch
$ git stash show -p stash@{0}
$ diff --git a/mission.html b/mission.html
    index b79f44d..6d6b92c 100644
    --- a/mission.html
    +++ b/mission.html
    @@ -15,7 +15,7 @@
       <div id="mainHeader">
         <a href="index.html" title="home" class="logo">
           <div id="logo">
-            <h1>Explore California</h1>
+            <h1>Explore California: Our Mission</h1>
           </div>
         </a>
        <div id="siteNav"> 
```

